SIMPLE: kindred
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kindred
<hw>Kin"dred</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>kinrede</ets>, <ets>kynrede</ets>, <ets>kunreden</ets> (with
excrescent <ets>d</ets>), fr. AS. <ets>cynn</ets> kin, race + the
termination <ets>-r⟦aemac⟧den</ets>, akin to AS. <ets>r⟦aemac⟧dan</ets>
to advise, G. <ets>rathen</ets>. Cf. <er>Hatred</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Relationship by birth or marriage; consanguinity; affinity;
kin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like her, of equal <qex>kindred</qex> to the throne.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Relatives by blood or marriage, more properly the
former; relations; persons related to each other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I think there's no man is secure⟦br⟧
But the queen's <qex>kindred</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Kin; kinsfolk; relatives; kinsmen; relations;
relationship; affinity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kindred</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Kindred
<hw>Kin"dred</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Related; congenial; of the like
nature or properties; <as>as, <ex>kindred</ex> souls; <ex>kindred</ex>
skies; <ex>kindred</ex> propositions.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>True to the <qex>kindred</qex> points of heaven and home.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kine</ent>⟦br⟧
